Create a folder called "fonts" inside the main folder. Place your desired font files into this folder.

Use the Win32 App Tool to package the main folder (which should include the "fonts" folder) into a Win32 app.

Install command: %windir%\sysnative\windowspowershell\v1.0\powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -file "installfonts.ps1"
Unintall command: %windir%\sysnative\windowspowershell\v1.0\powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -file "uninstallfont.ps1"
Detection: C:\Windows\Fonts\, file or folder: "your font file"